<p>The major thirds are correct, and two minor thirds are right, but D-F is not.</p>
<p>Another way to do it is as follows. We can insist that the chords D-F-A, A-C-E, and E-G-B be just <a href="/wiki/Minor_chord" title="Minor chord">minor triads</a> (then F-A-C and C-E-G are just <a href="/wiki/Major_chord" title="Major chord">major triads</a>, but G-B-D is not).</p>
<p>Then we get the following scale:</p>
