<p>The major thirds are correct, and two minor thirds are right, but B-D is not.</p>
<p>If we compare with the scale above, we see that six notes can be lined up, but one note, D, has changed its value. It is evidently not possible to get all six chords mentioned correct.</p>
<p>There are other possibilities; instead of lowering D, we can raise A. But this breaks something else.</p>
<p><a name="Twelve_tone_scale" id="Twelve_tone_scale"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Just_intonation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Twelve tone scale">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Twelve tone scale</span></h2>
<p>There are several ways to create a just tuning of the twelve tone scale.</p>
<p>The oldest known form of tuning, <a href="/wiki/Pythagorean_tuning" title="Pythagorean tuning">Pythagorean tuning</a>, can produce a twelve tone scale, but it does so by involving ratios of very large numbers, corresponding to natural harmonics very high in the harmonic series that do not occur widely in physical phenomena. This tuning uses ratios involving only powers of 3 and 2, creating a cycle of just <a href="/wiki/Perfect_fifth" title="Perfect fifth">perfect fifths</a>, as follows:</p>
<table class="wikitable" style="text-align: center">
<tr>
<th style="width:5em;">Note</th>
<th style="width:5em;">G<span class="music-symbol" style="font-family: Arial Unicode MS, Lucida Sans Unicode;">♭</span></th>
<th style="width:5em;">D<span class="music-symbol" style="font-family: Arial Unicode MS, Lucida Sans Unicode;">♭</span></th>
<th style="width:5em;">A<span class="music-symbol" style="font-family: Arial Unicode MS, Lucida Sans Unicode;">♭</span></th>
<th style="width:5em;">E<span class="music-symbol" style="font-family: Arial Unicode MS, Lucida Sans Unicode;">♭</span></th>
<th style="width:5em;">B<span class="music-symbol" style="font-family: Arial Unicode MS, Lucida Sans Unicode;">♭</span></th>
<th style="width:5em;">F</th>
<th style="width:5em;">C</th>
<th style="width:5em;">G</th>
<th style="width:5em;">D</th>
<th style="width:5em;">A</th>
<th style="width:5em;">E</th>
<th style="width:5em;">B</th>
<th style="width:5em;">F<span class="music-symbol" style="font-family: Arial Unicode MS, Lucida Sans Unicode;">♯</span></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Ratio</th>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{1024}{729}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/3/6/c/36c2f83babec79cb8d5ba1cc6a26ca77.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{256}{243}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/b/6/3/b63d2199c032153e624a720a000c2780.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{128}{81}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/a/7/8a7a2236a328ac2c5abe65b8469dc78c.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{32}{27}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/1/f/91fe9226f235654f1beef97fdd83b360.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{16}{9}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/2/5/a/25ac8d0fb223807b831e417cb11380af.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{4}{3}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/3/8/93853e11f4d8cd2d095ea23f1463e94b.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{1}{1}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/f/f/e/ffe2d660fee92aa531e7748247c278ac.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{3}{2}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/7/3/1/7317b62bf7533a6a642140a6d7f546ba.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{9}{8}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/0/1/80145f5d813f514043f2625869f8c021.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{27}{16}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/7/a/57abdb3ee57f533911e47319854bed34.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{81}{64}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/b/e/e/bee66475558b8596926eb3970e3b9b33.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{243}{128}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/b/8/e/b8ef280b6fb23af4acf460be3fb77f4f.png" /></td>
<td><img class="tex" alt="\frac{729}{512}" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/math/9/9/b/99b46572cf8bb6a917df3183d59067d3.png" /></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th>Cents</th>
<td>588.27</td>
<td>90.22</td>
<td>792.18</td>
<td>294.13</td>
<td>996.09</td>
